        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-09-15T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-09-15T18:00:00-05:00" n="411" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d411">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">863.01/9–1645: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Political Adviser for Austrian Affairs</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Erhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-09-16T00:00:00+01:00">September 16, 1945—12 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 1:08 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>219. We hear Soviets have notified Renner and Cabinet officers concerned that
                    they object to nationalization law and would not allow it to be published.
                    Soviets are reported to have taken similar attitude on all laws proposed by
                    Renner Cabinet re disposition of property. This is because they do not want
                    anything nationalized that might be German asset and claimable under Potsdam
                    communiqué.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Erhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
